  "pride_metadata": {
    "project": {
      "accession": "PXD035715",
      "title": "SARS-CoV-2 N protein interacts with cellular G3BP",
      "additionalAttributes": [],
      "projectDescription": "Severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus-2 (SARS-CoV-2) antagonizes stress granule formation, in part, via interaction between SARS-CoV-2 nucleocapsid (N) protein and Ras-GTPase-activating SH3-domain-binding protein 1 (G3BP1). In this study, we assessed interaction between the N protein of SARS-CoV-2 S clade and G3BP1 in Calu-3 cells",
      "sampleProcessingProtocol": "Calu-3 cells were cultured for 18 h at a density of 3 \u00d7 10^5 cells/well in 6-well plates. Cells were washed in PBS and infected with SARS-CoV-2 (S clade) at 0.1 multiplicity of infection (MOI) for 1 h, with shaking every 15 min, to allow adsorption of the virus, in a 5% CO2 incubator at 37\u00b0C. The supernatants were then aspirated and replaced with DMEM, containing 2% FBS. After 72 h infection, cells were washed with PBS and lysed for 30 min at 4\u00b0C in cell-lysis buffer (10 mM HEPES, 150 mM NaCl, 5 mM EDTA, 100 mM NaF, 2 mM Na3VO4, protease inhibitor cocktail, and 10% NP-40). Cell lysates were collected by centrifugation at 14,000 rpm at 4\u00b0C for 20 min and then incubated with anti-SARS-CoV-2 N mAb and Protein A beads (CaptivAtm PriMAB 52% [v/v] slurry; REPLIGEN, Waltham, MA, USA) for 2 h at 4\u00b0C. Anti-SARS-CoV-2 N mAb and Protein A bead immunocomplexes were collected by centrifugation and resolved by 4\u201312% gradient sodium dodecyl sulfate-polyacrylamide gel electrophoresis (SDS-PAGE) using Bolt\u2122 4\u201312% Bis\u2013Tris Plus gels (Thermo Fisher Scientific). Co-IP gels were stained with Coomassie brilliant blue G-250 or analyzed by western blot. After Co-IP with anti-SARS-CoV-2 N mAb, the protein bands of interest identified by 4\u201312% gradient SDS-PAGE were excised from gels and analyzed by Proteinworks Co (Seoul, South Korea). In brief, protein was digested with trypsin, and the resulting peptides were isolated using an Acclaim\u2122 PepMap\u2122 100 C18 LC Column (Thermo Fisher Scientific). These peptides were examined by tandem mass spectrometry (MS/MS), using a Q Exactive\u2122 Plus Hybrid Quadrupole-Orbitrap\u2122 Mass Spectrometer (Thermo Fisher Scientific).",
      "dataProcessingProtocol": "Data obtained were processed in Proteome Discoverer (PD, Thermo Fisher Scientific) v2.4. Fixed modifications included carbamidomethylation (Cys) and variable modifications included oxidation (Met) at peptide tolerance of 10 ppm and fragment tolerance of 0.02 Da. pdResult file generated by PD were analyzed against the UniProt human database including the sequence of the G3BP1 protein (Q13283).",
